- Develop a prototype tool that offers users interesting questions to ask about bits and pieces of text and learns iteratively about what the user is interested in while reading. 
- Consider generating bullet point outlines as a lead generation tool. 
- Incorporate an outline feature for any blog generated, such as a Wikipedia table of contents. 
- Notice what's missing and investigate problems further to develop solutions. 
- Don't focus on learning entrepreneurship in school, focus on becoming the Zen master who's naturally able to create beautiful art by being so at ease with yourself. 
- Remember that startups rarely die because of high competition. 
- Doing hard work that others find unappealing could be valued because people pay for it. 
- Don't turn off filters just to have ideas, but keep them as good habits to clear roadblocks between you and a good idea.